From 3d118d23bbaf99fa06d3a6df95ed50ad338929b5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ci7lus <7887955+ci7lus@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 16:58:34 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] demux/mpeg: Retry ProbeEnd from an earlier offset on
 immediate EOS

When ProbeEnd seeks to (stream_size - probe_window) and ReadTSPacket
returns NULL on the very first read (i_count == 1), the probe position
has landed at or past the actual end of TS content.  This can happen
when Content-Length includes trailing padding or when an HTTP server
reports a size slightly larger than the available data.

The previous code treated i_count < PROBE_CHUNK_COUNT uniformly as
"we have seen the entire tail" and broke out of the loop, causing
ProbeEnd to fail with no PCR found.

Distinguish the two cases:
 - i_count > 1: we read a partial tail; any PCR it contained has
   already been recorded.  Break as before.
 - i_count == 1: immediate EOF at the probe point; go one
   PROBE_CHUNK_COUNT step further back and retry, up to PROBE_MAX.
---
 modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c | 18 ++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c b/modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c
index 7b7b461f6eb..a7a28a058e1 100644
--- a/modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c
+++ b/modules/demux/mpeg/ts.c
@@ -2269,10 +2269,20 @@ int ProbeEnd( demux_t *p_demux, int i_program )
 
         int i_count = ProbeChunk( p_demux, i_program, true, &b_found );
         if( i_count < PROBE_CHUNK_COUNT )
-            break;
-
-        /* Go ahead one more chunk if end of file contained only stuffing packets */
-        i_probe_count += i_count;
+        {
+            /* i_count == 1 means ReadTSPacket returned NULL on the very first
+             * attempt after seeking: the probe position landed at or past the
+             * actual end of content (e.g. Content-Length includes trailing
+             * padding).  Try a further-back position before giving up. */
+            if( i_count > 1 )
+                break;
+            i_probe_count += PROBE_CHUNK_COUNT;
+        }
+        else
+        {
+            /* Go ahead one more chunk if end of file contained only stuffing packets */
+            i_probe_count += i_count;
+        }
     } while( i_pos > 0 && !b_found &&
              i_probe_count < PROBE_MAX );
 
-- 
